    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.36a.63_0001"/>
                
                <fw type="letterhead">
                    <hi rend="italics">Mrs. William Watkins
                    <lb/>
                    209 College Avenue
                    <lb/>
                    Swarthmore, Pa. 19081</hi>
                </fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>November 1, 1972</dateline>
                    
                    <salute>Dear Mrs. Young</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>Thank you for your quick and generous response to my request for information about Mr. Neihardt. It is much appreciated by our group of poetry lovers.</p>
                
                <p>I was especially glad to learn that recordings by Mr. Neihardt are available and have sent for the one in which he reads from "Lyric and Dramatic Poems". Since my program isn't scheduled until <unclear>April</unclear>, I'll have time to look for a copy of this book and also "A Cycle of The West."</p> 
                
                <p>Living with such a great <unclear>poet</unclear> must be a rewarding experience for you and I'm sure he appreciates your "care and 
                    
                    <fw type="curatorial">63</fw>
                    
                    <pb facs="nei.j4a.36a.63_0002"/>
                    
                    <fw type="authorial">-2-</fw>
                    
                    feeding" of himself and his poodle.</p>
                
                <p>I am wondering whether I could express my appreciation by making a painting of the poodle for its master. I can do this from photographs with acrylic paints on a six-inch plywood disc<del/>. My friends seem to like my animal portraits. I am 76 years old and have done art work all my adult life, including illustration &amp; portraits of people in <unclear>bas</unclear> relief or oil.</p> 
                <closer>
                    <salute>Again thanking you and Mr. Neihardt,</salute>
                    <salute>Sincerely yours,</salute>
                    
                    <signed>Hilda K. Watkins</signed>
                </closer>
                
                <note type="curatorial"><hi rend="caps">JOHN G. NEIHARDT CENTER</hi></note>
                
            </div1>
        </body>
        
